reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Shoe Rack
reviews.reviewText: I just separated from my wife and escaped to an apartment. My walk in at the old house had built in shoe cubbies for 30 pairs of mens shoes. My apartment walk in has zero shoe storage and I have a lot of shoes. I needed a solution with a combination of capacity, maximum height (to fit under my shirts), and maximum length. Two of these are perfect. I can use the wood top shelf for shoes too, the top wire shelf allows enough room for my boots, and the bottom shelf leaves enough room for all my flip flops under it on the carpet. Hoobro has a similar but lower cost 4 tier but it didn’t have enough room for the flip flops. I paid a fair amount more for this one because of that. This product was really easy to assemble and it looks great. I’m very happy with my purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice design and size, but it's a bit rickety
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I assembled it quickly and easily, but it is thin aluminum. Don't expect to be able to lean on it while you slip your shoes on. Get a little stool to sit on.Besides that, it's a great little stand for next to my front door. I have a little matching metal and wood motorcycle helmet stand on it, and a heavy black baking tray for my keys and things. A good addition to the pad so you don't walk around with dirty shoes.

reviews.reviewText: I originally purchased this as a temporary solution for my laundry room after my wall shelf decided to throw itself out of the wall and across the room.The quality is so much better than I expected, I probably won’t even rehang the original shelf. I am super happy with the product. It is very stable and worth the buy.

Great shoe shelf. I was worried there wouldn't be room for the doc martins but they fit on the first rack perfectly! If you have taller boots you can just remove one of the racks to fit them in. There's also enough room underneath for another row of shoes or sandals. We're able to fit 3 pairs on each rack and they're not crowded at all.The grates might get mucky with mud and snow in the wetter months but you can just put a tray in otherwise a drippy mess is unavoidable as this shelf does not defy the laws of gravity.My only (very) minor gripe is the upward lip at the back of each rack, if you have larger than size 10ish mens shoes/boots then they'll stick over the front edge a bit but you can slant them slightly if that bugs you. The racks can be installed to tilt down so the lip is needed to stop your shoes from sliding off...again with those pesky laws of gravity.Love that it has the shelf on top for baskets and such. This is exactly what we were looking for and the price was worth it compared to what you get elsewhere for a similar price. I'd recommend this for keeping your mudroom or entry way clutter free.
excellent quality, but remember that it is made for shoes, so although the top shelf is solid wood, the other shelves are wire mesh and don't support as much weight.
